  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Laparotomy wounds are associated with high rates of surgical site infections (SSI). The
      effect of prophylactic negative pressure dressing of closed incisional wounds on SSI rates is
      inconclusive.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
